data_table.description: Specimen Test Results - laboratory specimen analysis results and details

variable.name: TESTDY
variable.comment: Number of days from date of specimen draw to when the specimen was sent to the lab for testing.

variable.name: PULLID
variable.comment: The id of the study pull responsible for the test result. Pull ids are in the form xxx-yyy where xxx is the study id. A 'pull' is a set of vials pulled from the repository and shipped to one or more lab(s). A study will often have several pulls even if they only use a single lab. Multiple pulls are created to control workload and to limit the damage in case of shipping errors. Summary statistics for assays by pull can be found at www.whi.org in the specimen results page of the WHI data section.

variable.name: TESTVERID
variable.comment: Unique identifier of the test name and test version.

variable.name: TESTVER
variable.comment: A new version number is assigned for every change in lab, specimen type, units or method. e.g. if we have results from two different labs for a glucose assay, each would get its own version number. GLUC V1 & GLUC V2.

variable.name: TESTMTHD
variable.comment: Some test methods are not available.

variable.name: VERCOUNT
variable.description: Number of rows in result file for this test/version

variable.name: TESTVALMED
variable.comment: The median of TESTVAL in specimen results file (spec_results) for this test/version.

variable.name: TESTVALSTD
variable.comment: The standard deviation of TESTVAL in specimen results file (spec_results) for this test/version.

variable.name: NUMDUPPAIRS
variable.comment: Number of blind duplicate pairs used to calculate DUPAVGCV and DUPCORR. See the Specimen Results readme documentation for a discussion of 'blinded duplicate' samples used for QC.

variable.name: DUPCORR
variable.description: Coefficient of correlation of blinded duplicates
variable.comment: The correlation of result values over ALL duplicate pairs for this test version.

variable.name: DUPAVGCV
variable.description: Average Coefficient of Variation (%) of duplicate pairs
variable.comment: Coefficient of Variation (stddev/avg) is calculated for EACH duplicate pair.

variable.name: DUPMINCV
variable.description: Minumum Coefficient of Variation (%) of duplicate pairs
variable.comment: Coefficient of Variation (stddev/avg) is calculated for EACH duplicate pair.

variable.name: DUPMAXCV
variable.description: Maximum Coefficient of Variation (%) of duplicate pairs
variable.comment: Coefficient of Variation (stddev/avg) is calculated for EACH duplicate pair.
